mxTextCell.label:
Basic calculation functions:
1. add(a,b) adds the values of a and b2.
subtract(a,b) subtracts b from a
3. multiply(a,b) multiplies the values of a and b
4. divide(a,b) divides a by the value of b
5. mod(a,b) calculates the modulus of the division between a and b

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label:
Exponential functions:
1. square(a) returns the square value of a (a*a)
2. cube(a) returns the cubic value of a (a*a*a)
3. sqrt(a) returns the square root of a
4. cbrt(a) returns the cubic root of a
5. pow(a,b) returns the value of a raised to the power of b

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label:
Approximation and sign functions:
1. abs(a) returns the absolute value of a
2. floor(a) returns the closest integer value lower or equal than a
3. ceil(a) returns the closest integer value higher or equal than a
4. fix(a) returns the closest to 0 integer value of a"
5. sign(a) returns 1 if a is positive and -1 if a is negative

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label:
Logarithmic functions:
1. log2(a) returns the 2-base logarithm of a
2. log10(a) returns the 10-base logarithm of a
3. log(a) returns the logarithm value of a
4. log1p(a) returns the logarithm value of a+1
5. log(a,x) returns the x-base logarithm of a

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label:
Logical functions:
1. boolean(a) returns a as a boolean value
2. and(a,b) is 1 if both a and b are true, and 0 otherwise
3. or(a,b) is 1 if either a or b are true, and 0 if neither is true
4. not(a) is 1 if a is false and 0 if a is true
5. xor(a,b) is 1 if only a or only b is true, and 0 if both or neither are true

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label:
Relational functions:

2. equal(a,b) returns 1 if a=b and 0 otherwise
3. larger(a,b) returns 0 if ab
4. smaller(a,b) returns 1 if ab

mxTextCell.label:
Statistics functions:
